           <label>Name (English)</label>
          <name type="place" xml:lang="eng">Skoura</name>
          <label>MSA name</label>
          <name xml:lang="ara">سكورة</name>
          <label>MSA name (trans.)</label>
          <name xml:lang="ara-x-DMG">Sakūra</name>
          <label>Name in local variety (in transcription)</label>
          <name xml:lang="ara-x-DMG">Skūra</name>
            </head>

            <div type="positioning">
               <head>Geo location</head>
               <p>
                  <geo>31°03'N 06°33'W</geo>
                  <country>Morocco</country>
               </p>
            </div>
            <div type="typology">
               <head>Typology (Local)</head>
               <p rend="typology">West (Maghreb) › Morocco › Central type</p>
               <p>Hilalian-type sedentary rural dialect with strong influence of Berber</p>
            </div>

            <div type="general">
               <p>Skūra is an Arabic enclave in the Berber-speaking area south of the High Atlas. Many of the 15,000 inhabitants are bilingual. They live mainly on agriculture and stock breeding.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="researchHistory">
               <p>All available data on the dialect of Skūra is from the work of Jorge Aguadé and Mohammad Elyaâcoubi. <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:8SISG2GK">Aguadé 1994</rs> is a brief study on the formation of the reflexive-passive forms of the verb. <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:E3T3HBCD">Aguadé and Elyaacoubi 1995</rs> is a monograph on the dialect with chapters on phonology, nominal and verbal morphology, and verb paradigms. <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:I3FIKENT">Aguadé et al. 1996</rs> deals with the irrigation system in the oasis of Skūra, and the technical terminology concerning irrigation in the dialect of Skūra. Elyaâcoubi 1998 treats the topic of the classification of south Moroccan Arabic dialects on the example of Skūra, where a three page-grammatical sketch of the dialect is also provided.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="dictionaries">
               <p><rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:I3FIKENT">Aguadé et al. 1996</rs> includes a 2-page glossary of terminology related to the irrigation system (<hi rendition="#i">xiṭṭāra</hi>).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography">               
                    <p xml:space="preserve">To view publications on this variety click <rs type="bibl" ref="bibl:geo:Skoura">here</rs>.</p>
